  "description": [
    "l itWWf J5 The President Places the Cuban Matter Before Congress He Asks for Authority to Put a to the War in the Island Stop But Advises Against Recognizing the Insurgent Government at the Present Time Cites Many Illustrious Precedents for This RecommendationSays The War Must Stop Refers to the Battleship Maine Ex plosion as a Sign of Spanish Weaknes s Washington April llThe president Monday sent the following message to the congress of the United States Obedient to that precept of the constitu tion which commands the president to give from time to time tocongress information of the state of the union and to recom mend to their consideration such measures i he shall judge necessary and expedient it becomes my duty now to address your body with regard to the grave crisis that has arisen in the relations of the United States to Spain by reason of the warfare that for more than three years has raged in the neighboring island of Cuba 1 do so because of the intimate connection of the Cuban question with the state of our own union and the grave relation the course which it is now incumbent upon the nation to adopt"
